+# False Positive Report: CVE-2026-7722
+
+## Summary
+
+CVE-2026-7722 does **not** affect PrefectHQ/prefect version **2.14.13**. This is a confirmed false positive. The vulnerable code path was introduced nearly a year after version 2.14.13 was released.
+
+---
+
+## CVE Details
+
+| Field | Value |
+|-------|-------|
+| CVE ID | CVE-2026-7722 |
+| Severity | High |
+| CWE | CWE-287 (Improper Authentication) |
+| Component | Health Check API (`/api/health`) |
+| Affected File | `src/prefect/server/api/server.py` |
+| Reported Affected Versions | PrefectHQ/prefect up to 3.6.21 |
+| Fixed Version | 3.6.22 |
+| Fix Commit | `e21617125335025b4b27e7d6f0ca028e8e8f3b79` |
+
+---
+
+## Vulnerability Description
+
+The vulnerability exists in the `token_validation` HTTP middleware inside `create_api_app()` in `src/prefect/server/api/server.py`. The middleware was introduced as part of the `PREFECT_SERVER_API_AUTH_STRING` Basic Auth feature.
+
+The vulnerable code used Python's `str.endswith()` to exempt health check paths from authentication:
+
+```python
+# VULNERABLE code (never present in 2.14.x)
+if (
+    request.url.path.endswith(("health", "ready"))
+    and request.method.upper() == "GET"
+):
+    return await call_next(request)
+```
+
+This had two weaknesses:
+1. **Suffix matching bypass** — any path ending in `health` or `ready` (e.g., `/api/variables/name/system-health`) bypassed authentication.
+2. **Host header spoofing** — a crafted `Host` header could manipulate `request.url.path`, making the check evaluate against an attacker-controlled path.
+
+The fix (commit `e21617125335025b4b27e7d6f0ca028e8e8f3b79`) replaced suffix matching with exact path matching using `scope["path"]`:
+
+```python
+# FIXED code
+health_check_paths = {health_check_path, "/ready"}
+scope = request.scope
+app_path = scope["path"].removeprefix(scope.get("root_path", ""))
+if app_path in health_check_paths and request.method.upper() == "GET":
+    return await call_next(request)
+```
+
+---
+
+## Why This Is a False Positive for Version 2.14.13
+
+### Timeline
+
+| Event | Date | Commit |
+|-------|------|--------|
+| Version 2.14.13 released | 2024-01-04 | `9df5ba721c` |
+| `PREFECT_SERVER_API_AUTH_STRING` feature introduced | 2024-12-16 | `9af5624920` |
+| CVE-2026-7722 fix released (v3.6.22) | 2026 | `e21617125` |
+
+Version 2.14.13 was released on **January 4, 2024**. The `PREFECT_SERVER_API_AUTH_STRING` Basic Auth feature — which contains the vulnerable `token_validation` middleware — was not introduced until **December 16, 2024** (commit `9af56249209abb8d3b0201a4c2957949926b8508`), nearly **12 months later**.
+
+### Proof: Vulnerable Code Does Not Exist in 2.14.13
+
+The following git command confirms that `src/prefect/server/api/server.py` in the `2.14.13` tag contains no reference to `AUTH_STRING`, `auth_string`, or `token_validation`:
+
+```bash
+git show 2.14.13:src/prefect/server/api/server.py | grep -n "AUTH_STRING\|auth_string\|token_validation"
+# (no output)
+```
+
+The `PREFECT_SERVER_API_AUTH_STRING` setting and the accompanying middleware simply do not exist in the 2.14.x codebase. There is no authentication middleware to bypass, and therefore no attack surface for this vulnerability.
+
+### Why the Scanner Flagged It
+
+Automated vulnerability scanners typically match CVEs against package name and version range. CVE-2026-7722 is associated with the `prefect` PyPI package, and scanners may flag all versions without verifying whether the specific vulnerable feature was present in a given release. The CVE advisory itself states the affected range as "up to 3.6.21", which refers exclusively to the 3.x series.
+
+---
+
+## Conclusion
+
+| | |
+|--|--|
+| **Is 2.14.13 vulnerable?** | No |
+| **Does the vulnerable code exist in 2.14.13?** | No |
+| **Recommended action** | Mark as false positive; no patch or upgrade required for 2.14.13 |
+
+The `PREFECT_SERVER_API_AUTH_STRING` feature and the `token_validation` middleware were introduced exclusively in the 3.x line. Version 2.14.13 is not susceptible to CVE-2026-7722.
